# Cloudflare Pages response headers. The Content-Security-Policy ships as a <meta>
# tag in index.html (so it applies to the desktop build too) — these are the
# security headers a meta tag CAN'T set. Deliberately NO Permissions-Policy here:
# the web app needs camera / microphone / display-capture for voice calls, which
# are allowed for the top-level origin by default.
/*
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
